text: Krystsina Siarheyeuna Tsimanouskaya (; born 19 November 1996) is a Belarusian sprinter. She won a silver medal in the 100 metres at the 2017 European U23 Championships. She also won a gold medal in the 200 metres at the 2019 Summer Universiade. ==International competitions== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing |- |rowspan=2|2015 |rowspan=2|European Junior Championships |rowspan=2|Eskilstuna, Sweden |6th |100 m |11.85 |- |17th (h) |200 m |24.51 |- |rowspan=3|2017 |European Indoor Championships |Belgrade, Serbia |12th (sf) |60 m |7.39 |- |rowspan=2|European U23 Championships |rowspan=2|Bydgoszcz, Poland |bgcolor=silver|2nd |100 m |11.54 |- |4th |200 m |23.32 |- |rowspan=3|2018 |World Indoor Championships |Birmingham, United Kingdom |31st (h) |60 m |7.37 |- |rowspan=2|European Championships |rowspan=2|Berlin, Germany |13th (sf) |100 m |11.34 |- |10th (sf) |200 m |23.03 |- |rowspan=4|2019 |European Indoor Championships |Glasgow, United Kingdom |7th |60 m |7.26 |- |rowspan=2|Universiade |rowspan=2|Naples, Italy |6th |100 m |11.44 |- |bgcolor=gold|1st |200 m |23.00 |- |World Championships |Doha, Qatar |26th (h) |200 m |23.22 |} ==Personal bests== Outdoor *100 metres – 11.28 (+1.4 m/s, Ellwangen 2017) *200 metres – 23.00 (+1.0 m/s, Neapol 2019) Indoor *60 metres – 7.21 (Mogilyov 2017) *200 metres – 23.66 (Mogilyov 2017) 100 metres -11.09 (Belarus 2018) 200 metres- 22.78 ( Minsk 2019) ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian female sprinters Category:European Games competitors for Belarus Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games medalists in athletics Category:European Games silver medalists for Belarus Category:Universiade gold medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:Universiade gold medalists for Belarus Category:Medalists at the 2019 Summer Universiade
